                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the scribe; a few lines on the incipit page of the text, alternating with black lines; two initial lines of each section of the text; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; parts of abbreviations; quire marks; some other words, e.g., ṣällǝyu (e.g., fols. 7vb, 8ra, 9va),  wä-kaʿǝbä (e.g., fols. 7vb, 38ra, 55ra), tәʾәzaz (e.g., fols. 13rb, 14va, 17rb), wä-yǝbälu (fols. 15va, 16rb), wä-ʾәmzә (e.g.,fols. 16ra, 30ra, 32vb).</rubric>
